WELCOME TO THE CS 4920/5920 CAPTURE THE FLAG (CTF)


With increasing cyber control, threats, and issues, cybersecurity is getting increasingly important. Let’s form a security team. The following are the tasks that are outlined for the security team.

CTF pre-registration: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScD-LOzExRPV8w5qRrsi6E1mjmk16uLvQPkeWUL2ESwC35tqw/viewform?usp=sf_link.

  • INVESTIGATION Investigate the real-world security attacks on metros and public transportation and the state of the art research and designs in metro security, and identify and evaluate the security risks for different threats
  • DESIGN Select the required security objectives and design the corresponding security mechanisms
  • ANALYSIS Analyze the overheads, vulnerabilities and threats of the proposed security mechanisms
  • IMPLEMENTATION Implement the security mechanisms in software/programming as well as on hardware
  • TESTING AND EVALUATION Construct the networking- and computing-testbeds for simulation and testing
  • COORDINATION Oversee the entire team process, and communicate with external stakeholders (e.g., the System Integrator, state and city officials)

    • Instruction:

    In the Challenges page, you will see some tasks waiting for you. Try to finish as many as you can.
    If you have any questions or need any help, please visit one of the breakout rooms in the call.

    Zoom link: https://uccs-edu.zoom.us/j/4631789836?pwd=Ujh5SkZIS0k0Tm92T1pVbzh4Uzg2QT09
